}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kriegfrj/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kriegfrj/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kriegfrj/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kriegfrj/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kriegfrj/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kriegfrj/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"subscribed","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2022-03-07T02:46:02Z","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/1060439763","html_url":"https://github.com/assertj/assertj/issues/2504#issuecomment-1060439763","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/2504","id":1060439763,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAIX3Vs4_NQbT","user":{"login":"joel-costigliola","id":382613,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4MjYxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/382613?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola","html_url":"https://github.com/joel-costigliola","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-03-07T10:18:47Z","updated_at":"2022-03-07T10:18:47Z","body":"I think adding `assertThat` for each interface type and use `AssertionsForClassTypes` should address the issue, note that one will not be able to static import every potentially ambiguous `assertThat` as shown in the test below:\r\n```java\r\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.AssertionsForClassTypes.assertThat;\r\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.PredicateAssert.assertThat;\r\n\r\nimport java.util.function.Predicate;\r\n\r\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\r\n\r\nclass Assertions_solving_assertThat_ambiguous_Test {\r\n\r\n  @Test\r\n  void should_resolve_ambiguous_assertThat_for_interfaces_and_use_assertThat_for_classes() {\r\n    // GIVEN\r\n    ComparablePredicate<String> comparablePredicate = new ComparablePredicate<>();\r\n    // WHEN/THEN\r\n    // can't static import both PredicateAssert.assertThat and GenericComparableAssert.assertThat \r\n    assertThat(comparablePredicate).isNotNull();\r\n    GenericComparableAssert.assertThat(comparablePredicate).isNotNull();\r\n    // can use assertThat for classes without issue\r\n    assertThat(\"\").isEmpty();\r\n    assertThat(2L).isPositive();\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  static class ComparablePredicate<T> implements Comparable<T>, Predicate<T> {\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public boolean test(T t) {\r\n      return false;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public int compareTo(T o) {\r\n      return 0;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/1060439763/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"joel-costigliola","id":382613,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4MjYxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/382613?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joel-costigliola","html_url":"https://github.com/joel-costigliola","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/use