y":"> note that one will not be able to static import every potentially ambiguous `assertThat`\r\n\r\nwhat about the first suggestion of adding `assert[InterfaceName]`?\r\nthese methods don't have to be added in `AssertionsForClassTypes` / `AssertionsForInterfaceTypes` if you want to prevent it from having too many methods;\r\nit is also fine in each Interface implementation like `GenericComparableAssert`\r\nlike that, we can still import the methods statically\r\n_(you can do these also additionally to the other plan you presented above)_","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/1062234799/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"rala72","id":6838669,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4Mzg2Njk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6838669?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72","html_url":"https://github.com/rala72","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rala72/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/comments/1062407438","html_url":"https://github.com/assertj/assertj/issues/2504#issuecomment-1062407438","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/assertj/assertj/issues/2504","id":1062407438,"node_